sql:
SELECT AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM products
WHERE platform_id = (SELECT platform_id FROM platforms WHERE platform_name = 'Amazon');

SELECT products.product_name, platforms.platform_name 
FROM products 
INNER JOIN platforms ON products.platform_id = platforms.platform_id;

SELECT platform_id, AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM products
GROUP BY platform_id;

external_knowledge:
- Enthusiastic, high-rating users are those with an average rating above 4.5; 
- The context of "high-rated products" refers to products with a rating greater than 4;
- Products must be available for purchase on Amazon and belong to the Electronics category.
